      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:190:1",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " لَيْسَ شَيْ‏ءٌ تَحْضُرُهُ الْمَلَائِكَةُ إِلَّا الرِّهَانُ وَ مُلَاعَبَةُ الرَّجُلِ أَهْلَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Ahmad Bin Is’haq, from Sa’dan Bin Muslim, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There is nothing which the Angels attend except the horse-racing and the playing of the man with his wife’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Abu Ali al-Ash’ariy has narrated from Ahmad ibn Ishaq from Sa’dan ibn Muslim from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘No other thing is attended by the angel as horse racing is and a man’s playing with his wife.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
